September Intake to Study in the UK: Timeline, Courses, University's Requirements

  • 1444 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Apr 28,2023 05:53 PM IST

Planning to apply for September 2023 intake in the UK but don’t know where to start from? Check out the blog below for detailed information on September intake, including deadlines, admission requirements and courses offered by top universities.

The UK has undoubtedly remained a popular study destination among international students. The country houses some of the world’s oldest academic institutes, having their roots in the 12th and 13th centuries. With its prestigious universities and colleges, high-quality education and innovative learning approach, the academic experiences one gets while studying in the UK are hard to beat.

Students planning to study in the UK should note that the country accepts admissions for three intakes: September (Fall), January (Winter), and May (Summer). Among all the intakes, September is the most preferred intake by international students as most universities and colleges accept admissions for this session and offer a wide variety of courses.

Below is a detailed description of the timeline for the September intake, including types of intakes and popular universities accepting admissions for this intake.

Step-by-Step Guide to Apply for UK Universities September Intake:

Following are the steps to apply for education in the UK:

•Schedule counselling session

Begin the process by scheduling a counselling session with an expert counsellor who can help search and shortlist the university/program that best suits the candidate's profile

•Acquire details about requirements

Visit the university website, check out the application requirements, tuition fee, deadlines, etc., of the chosen university/program, and proceed accordingly

•Prepare and give standardized tests

Based on the course guidelines, start preparing for and give required standardized tests such as GRE, GMAT, IELTS, TOEFL etc.

•Draft SOP and essays

Carefully prepare you statement of purpose and any other essays as these play a crucial role in profile selection

•Submit applications

Send in applications to the admission department of the shortlisted institute by highlighting the strengths and other achievements

•Respond to acceptance letters

Wait for the university email and reply when these are received
Pay the non-refundable deposit to confirm the admission

•Apply for scholarships/financial aid

Search and apply for scholarships or other financial assistance if the institute offers
Apply for a student loan if required

•Visa work

Start the paperwork for the student visa and book airline tickets on receiving it

•Prepare for finances abroad

Arrange for an international debit/credit card

•Prepare documents before travelling

Make sure to take the original and copies of the required documents before travelling

Things to Keep in Mind for a Successful Application:

1.Choose the course and university wisely. Applying for programs that best match a student’s potential is a tedious task requiring research. So it is important to start the process early.
2.Carefully make a list of all the necessary documents required in the process and gather them in the given time.
3.Timely prepare and attempt the tests required for application, such as English proficiency tests or entrance tests.
4.Spend time framing the most authentic Statement of Purpose (SOP) and Letter of Recommendation. Writing a plagiarized personal statement may lead to rejection of the application.
5.Customize the personal statement as per the requirements of the applied institute and carefully check the information provided in the application before submitting.
6.Apply for scholarships based on the profile to reduce the financial burden.

Documents Required to Study in the UK

In order to apply for education in the UK, international students are required to submit documents based on the requirements of the institute they choose to apply for. However, there are a few standard documents that every student has to submit, such as:

Undergraduate
•Passport
•Academic Transcripts
•Certificate of Graduation
•Certificate of English Proficiency- IELTS/TOEFL/PTE
•Statement of Purpose
•Letter of Recommendation
•CV (if applicable)
Postgraduate
•Certificate of Graduation/ Bachelor’s Degree

PhD/ Research
•Certificate of Graduation/ Master’s Degree
•Research Proposal

Reasons Why Fall Intake is Popular to Study in the UK

September is considered to be the primary intake for the majority of UK universities. International students apply for this intake as they get to choose from a wide range of courses. Students applying for this intake also get the advantage of the availability of more scholarships and internship opportunities.
Note: Since September is a popular intake, students planning to study in the UK are suggested to make the application well in time.

To know more about the courses available in this intake, click here.

How to Choose the Right UK Intake
It is vital to select the right intake based on one’s own profile and requirements. Thus, one shouldn’t rush the process and make a list of pros and cons before making their choice. Additionally, consulting an expert is always beneficial in case of any doubts. Contact Canam Consultants today to learn more.  

FAQ

What are the entry requirements for UK universities?

The admission requirements of every university in the UK differ in one way or another, however, some of the typical requirements are:
•Academic certificates of previously attended courses.
•Proof of English language proficiency.

When to Apply for September Intake in UK 2023?

It is suggested to start the application process for September intake in the UK a year prior. The deadline for universities accepting admissions for Fall intake is somewhere between February and April of the same year.

What factors should be kept in mind before applying for study in the UK?

Before making an application to UK universities, it is important to have the test scores ready along with the required documents and finances that are sufficient to support the expenses. Students should also do some research on accommodation.

Which intake is better to study in the UK?

Out of all the intakes, September intake is the most popular intake as all the undergraduate and postgraduate courses and available in this session.

How much gap is acceptable to study in the UK?

Students with a study gap of not more than 2 years can apply to any UK university for a bachelor’s degree.
